    <!-- 08 Section header -->
    <section class="sg-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="sg-section-head">
          <span class="sg-index">08 / section header</span>
          <h2>Band section header</h2>
          <p class="sg-note">Every content band opens with a mono section number, a 900-weight heading, and a 2px black rule beneath. A 300-weight intro follows.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="sg-panel">
          <div class="section-header">
            <span class="section-number">01</span>
            <h2>Workflows</h2>
          </div>
          <p class="section-intro">Architecture problems are not discovered in theory — they are discovered while working. AtlasArc fits the IDE workflow you already have.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 09 Cards -->
    <section class="sg-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="sg-section-head">
          <span class="sg-index">09 / cards</span>
          <h2>Cards</h2>
          <p class="sg-note">Two treatments. The default bordered card — a white panel with a 1px border and an outgoing-arc glyph, going navy on hover. And the open workflow-card row — a top-ruled four-column band divided by hairlines, first card flush to the edge.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="card-grid">
          <li class="card"><a href="#09"><h3>Find cyclic dependencies</h3><p>Detect, inspect, and untangle cycles between packages.</p></a></li>
          <li class="card"><a href="#09"><h3>Review package boundaries</h3><p>Spot boundary erosion before it sets like concrete.</p></a></li>
          <li class="card"><a href="#09"><h3>Identify risky hotspots</h3><p>See where change concentration meets complexity.</p></a></li>
        </ul>
        <div class="sg-demo">
          <div class="sg-type-label" style="margin-bottom:1rem">Open workflow cards — top-ruled four-column row</div>
          <ul class="wf-grid">
            <li><a class="wf-card" href="#09"><h3>Find cyclic dependencies</h3><p>Detect the dependency loops that block refactoring before they compound.</p></a></li>
            <li><a class="wf-card" href="#09"><h3>Review package boundaries</h3><p>See which packages cross intended architectural boundaries.</p></a></li>
            <li><a class="wf-card" href="#09"><h3>Identify risky hotspots</h3><p>Find the packages absorbing the most change pressure and complexity.</p></a></li>
            <li><a class="wf-card" href="#09"><h3>Understand subsystem coupling</h3><p>Plot subsystems in metric space to see which parts are stable.</p></a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 10 Lens grid -->
    <section class="sg-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="sg-section-head">
          <span class="sg-index">10 / lenses</span>
          <h2>Contained lens grid</h2>
          <p class="sg-note">The five analytical lenses. A single outer border wraps the row so it never hugs the band edge; each cell carries a 3px navy top accent and a mono lens type.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="lens-grid">
          <li class="lens-card">
            <span class="lens-type">Structural</span>
            <h3>Topology</h3>
            <p>Understand how the architecture is connected. Inline expansion without losing context.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="lens-card">
            <span class="lens-type">Relational</span>
            <h3>Matrix</h3>
            <p>Inspect exact dependency relationships. Spot coupling patterns and cycles at a glance.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="lens-card">
            <span class="lens-type">Hierarchical</span>
            <h3>Composition</h3>
            <p>Explore the architecture by area and mass. Treemap, sunburst, circle pack.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="lens-card">
            <span class="lens-type">Metric-space</span>
            <h3>Subsystems</h3>
            <p>Plot subsystems in abstract metric space. Find stable cores and the risky periphery.</p>
          </li>
          <li class="lens-card">
            <span class="lens-type">Metric-space</span>
            <h3>Hotspots</h3>
            <p>Find the packages absorbing the most change pressure, coupling, and complexity.</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 11 Metric cards -->
    <section class="sg-section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="sg-section-head">
          <span class="sg-index">11 / metrics</span>
          <h2>Clickable metric cards</h2>
          <p class="sg-note">Individually bordered, separated by a gap, with a mono label and an arrow that slides on hover — clearly navigable, distinct from the static card grid.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="metrics-grid">
          <li><a class="metric-card" href="#11">
            <span class="metric-label">Structural</span>
            <h3>Cyclic dependencies</h3>
            <p>Count and classify dependency cycles. See which packages are entangled and which form the cycle core.</p>
          </a></li>
          <li><a class="metric-card" href="#11">
            <span class="metric-label">Coupling</span>
            <h3>Fan-in and fan-out</h3>
